  <data name="Home.Faq.Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Everything you want to know</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq.Lead" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>No fine print. If we don&apos;t answer it here, just ask when you sign up.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq1.Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Do I need to know music theory to start?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq1.A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>No. Academia Auditiva guides you from zero, with introductory exercises and tips at every step. If you already know theory, the platform adapts to your level.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq2.Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Does it work on mobile?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq2.A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Yes, it works. The platform is fully web and responsive — just open it in your phone, tablet or computer browser. Nothing to install.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq3.Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Which languages are available?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq3.A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Portuguese (Brazil), English and French. You can switch language anytime in the menu.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq4.Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>I&apos;m a teacher. How do I create a class?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq4.A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>After creating your account with a teacher profile, you get a panel to create classes, generate invitation links and build weekly routines for each student.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq5.Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>What repertoire do the exercises cover?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq5.A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Note perception, major and minor chords, chord quality (including diminished, augmented and tetrachords), melodic and harmonic intervals, harmonic function and rhythm reading.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq6.Q" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Is it really free?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Home.Faq6.A" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Yes — you can create an account and train without paying anything. Advanced features for teachers and classes remain available during the launch period.</value>
  </data>
